    "comment": "Rationale: In this study, Zhao et al knocked down (KD) SCAMP5 in primary cultured neurons using shRNA. SypHy, a fusion protein of synaptophysin with pHluorin was used to measure the kinetics of exo- and endocytosis. Synaptic vesicle (SV) endocytosis during stimulation was severely defective in the SCAMP5 KD neurons and was fully rescued by the expression of HA-SCAMP5 resistant to shRNA (Fig. 6A-D).. Experimental description: Hippocampal neurons derived from embryonic day 18 Sprague Dawley fetal rats of either sex were prepared as described previously (Chang and De Camilli, 2001).",
